# exclude respons from data frame before starting multiple imputation

Define IPI score
# create long format
# include = logical to indicate whether the original data with the missing values should be included
DLBCL.long <- mice::complete(DLBCL, action="long", include=T)

# calculate IPI score after imputation
DLBCL.long$ipi_score <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$lft>60) + DLBCL.long$ipi_ldh + DLBCL.long$ipi_ps +
  as.numeric(DLBCL.long$stadium!=2) + DLBCL.long$ipi_extra
DLBCL.long$ipi_score[DLBCL.long$ipi_score==0] <- 1
DLBCL.long$ipi_score[DLBCL.long$ipi_score==5] <- 4
Define some variables binary instead of categorical after imputation
DLBCL.long$stage2 <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$stadium==2)
DLBCL.long$stage3 <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$stadium==3)
DLBCL.long$stage4 <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$stadium==4)
for (regio in 1:9){
  DLBCL.long[, paste0("region", regio)] <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$region==regio)
}
DLBCL.long$ses.low <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$sescat==0)
DLBCL.long$ses.medium <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$sescat==1)
DLBCL.long$ses.high <- as.numeric(DLBCL.long$sescat==2)
Define time at which patients are at risk, which is the end of the possible 8th cycle (second additional rituximab treatment).
# add 63 days for 6x R-CHOP21    (RCHOP21==0)
# add 42 days for 6x R-CHOP21+1R (RCHOP21==9)
# add 21 days for 6x R-CHOP21+2R (RCHOP21==1) because txstop_rit is almost at the start of the cycle
DLBCL.long <- DLBCL.long |>
  mutate(
    at.risk.42 = case_when(
      RCHOP21==0 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(63),  # 6x R-CHOP21
      RCHOP21==9 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(42),  # 6x R-CHOP21 + 1R
      RCHOP21==1 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(21)), # 6x R-CHOP21 + 2R
    at.risk.90 = case_when(
      RCHOP21==0 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(90),  # 6x R-CHOP21
      RCHOP21==9 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(69),  # 6x R-CHOP21 + 1R
      RCHOP21==1 ~ as.Date(DLBCL.long$txstop_rit) + lubridate::days(48))) # 6x R-CHOP21 + 2R

Add 6x R-CHOP21 + 1R to the 6x R-CHOP21 + 2R group

DLBCL.long$RCHOP21[DLBCL.long$RCHOP21==9] <- 1

Perform analyses for two different landmarks

limit_year <- 5
for (landmark in c(42, 90)){
  # Define recurrence and survival time measured from the date at which 
  # the first additional rituximab cycle could have been administered (at.risk) 
  # and the date of event-free survival (efsdat)
  at.risk <- eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL$at.risk.", landmark)))
  single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time <- as.numeric(difftime(as.Date(single.imp.DLBCL$efsdat), 
                                                   at.risk, unit="weeks"))/52
  single.imp.DLBCL$OS.time <- as.numeric(difftime(as.Date(single.imp.DLBCL$osdat), 
                                                  at.risk, unit="weeks"))/52
  
  # display number of excluded patients
  cat(" Landmark at", landmark, "days", "\n",
      "Total number of patients with death before date at risk:", 
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$OS.time<0), "\n",
      "Total number of patients with event before date at risk:", 
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0), "\n",
      "Number of patients treated with 6x R-CHOP21 with death before date at risk:",
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$OS.time<0&single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21==0), "\n",
      "Number of patients treated with 6x R-CHOP21 with event before date at risk:", 
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0&single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21==0), "\n",
      "Number of patients treated with 6x R-CHOP21 + 2R with death before date at risk:", 
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$OS.time<0&single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21==1), "\n",
      "Number of patients treated with 6x R-CHOP21 + 2R with event before date at risk:", 
      sum(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0&single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21==1), "\n")
  
  # exclude patients before landmark 
  omit.before.landmark <- which(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0)
  single.imp.DLBCL.landmark <- single.imp.DLBCL[-omit.before.landmark,]
  cat(" Number of included patients at", landmark, "day landmark", 
      nrow(single.imp.DLBCL.landmark), " \n")
  
  # save for descriptives
  if (landmark==42){
    # omit events before landmark
    descriptives.data <- to.be.imputed.DLBCL[-omit.before.landmark,]
    
    # add treatment response
    descriptives.data$respons <- tx_response[-omit.before.landmark]
    
    # add 1R to 2R
    descriptives.data$RCHOP21[descriptives.data$RCHOP21==9] <- 1
    
    # save file to create descriptives
    save(descriptives.data, 
         file=paste0(file.path, "Data/descriptives.data.Rdata"), compress=TRUE)  
  }
  
  # Propensity score model
  # 1. RCHOP21 indicates whether the patient received 6x R-CHOP21 or 6x R-CHOP21+2R.
  # 2. region indicates the region where the patient is treated.
  # 3. The International Prognostic Index (IPI) consists of 
  #   + an indicator of age > 60 (lft)
  #   + stage 3 or 4 (stadium)
  #   + elevated serum LDH (ipi_ldh)
  #   + WHO score ECOG/Zubrod status 2, 3, or 4 (ipi_ps)
  #   + more than 1 extranodal site (ipi_extra).
  # 4. malignancy indicates if a patient had one or more previous malignancy
  # 5. center indicates if the center that the patient is treated in was academic or not
  # 6. ses indicates Social Economic Status, which is a proxy for comorbidity, 
  # and is divided into low, medium, and high.
  
  # fixed effects propensity score model
  PS.formula <- RCHOP21~geslacht+lft+stadium+ipi_ldh+ipi_ps+ipi_extra+
    malignancy+region+center+ses.low+ses.high
  PS.model <- fit.mult.impute(PS.formula, lrm,
                              xtrans=DLBCL,
                              data=to.be.imputed.DLBCL,
                              subset=-omit.before.landmark,
                              n.impute=m, pr=FALSE, fit.reps=TRUE,
                              y=TRUE, x=TRUE, se.fit=TRUE)
  print(anova(fit.mult.impute(RCHOP21~geslacht+lft+stadium+ipi_ldh+ipi_ps+ipi_extra+
    malignancy+region+center+sescat, lrm,
                              xtrans=DLBCL,
                              data=to.be.imputed.DLBCL,
                              subset=-omit.before.landmark,
                              n.impute=m, pr=FALSE, fit.reps=TRUE,
                              y=TRUE, x=TRUE, se.fit=TRUE)))

  # Compute the propensity score ($e_i$), i.e. the predicted probability of 
  # treatment, averaged over multiple imputations. 
  P.Z <- mean(single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21)
  e.i.imp <- c()
  stabilized.w.i.imp <- c()
  for (imp in 1:m){
    # propensity score for ith imputed data set
    e.i.imp <- cbind(e.i.imp, plogis(predict(PS.model$fits[[imp]], type="lp", 
                                             subset=-omit.before.landmark,
                                             newdata=mice::complete(DLBCL, imp))))
    # compute stabilized inverse propensity score weights for ith imputed data set
    stabilized.w.i.imp <- cbind(stabilized.w.i.imp, 
                            P.Z*single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21/e.i.imp[, imp] +
                            (1-P.Z)*(1-single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21)/(1-e.i.imp[, imp]))
  }
  
  # Difference between stabilized and unstabilized propensity score weights
  plot(x=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21/rowMeans(e.i.imp)+
         (1-single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21)/(1-rowMeans(e.i.imp)), 
     y=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp), 
     xlab="Unstabilized", ylab="Stabilized")
  
  # Assess the performance of the propensity score model.
  show(rms::val.prob(rowMeans(e.i.imp), single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21, g=10))
  
  # Write Propensity Score Model Table to Excel
  names <- c("Intercept",
             "Females",
             "Parameters of the IPI-score",
             "   Age (77 versus 63 years)",
             "   Ann Arbor stage",
             "      II",
             "      III",
             "      IV",
             "   Elevated serum LDH",
             "   Performance status",
             "   > 1 extranodal site",
             "> 1 previous malignancy",
             "Regions",
             "   Region 1",
             "   Region 2",
             "   Region 3",
             "   Region 4",
             "   Region 5",
             "   Region 6",
             "   Region 7",
             "   Region 8",
             "   Region 9",
             "Treatment at an academic center",
             "Socioeconomic Status",
             "   Low",
             "   Medium",
             "   High")
  summary.PS <- summary(PS.model, 
                        region=1, 
                        stadium=2)[which(summary(PS.model, 
                                                 region=1, 
                                                 stadium=2)[, "Type"]==2), 
                          c("Effect", "Lower 0.95", "Upper 0.95")]
  values <- data.frame(coefficients=sprintf("%.2f", summary.PS[,"Effect"]),
                       CI=paste0(sprintf("%.2f", summary.PS[,"Lower 0.95"]), "-", 
                                 sprintf("%.2f", summary.PS[,"Upper 0.95"])))
  values.table <- rbind(values[1,],     # geslacht
                        "",
                        values[2,],     # lft
                        "",             # stage
                        c("(ref)", ""),
                        values[10:11,],
                        values[3:6,],   # LDH, PS, extra, malignancy
                        "",             # region
                        c("(ref)", ""), 
                        values[12:19,],
                        values[7,],     # center
                        "",             # SES
                        values[8,],
                        c("(ref)", ""),
                        values[9,])
  PS.table <- data.frame(names=names, 
                         OR=c(sprintf("%.2f", exp(PS.model$coefficients[1])), 
                              values.table[, "coefficients"]),
                         CI=c(paste0(sprintf("%.2f", 
                                             exp(PS.model$coefficients[1]+
                                                   qnorm(0.025)*sqrt(PS.model$var[1,1]))), 
                                     "-",
                                     sprintf("%.2f", 
                                             exp(PS.model$coefficients[1]+
                                                   qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(PS.model$var[1,1])))),
                              values.table[, "CI"]))
  openxlsx::write.xlsx(PS.table,
             file=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/Table S2.at.landmark.", landmark, ".xlsx"))
  
  ##### Check overlap assumption
  # orange: #EC7F12
  # purple: #9161BD
  # blue: #0D88AF
  overlap.assumption.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(single.imp.DLBCL.landmark, 
                                             ggplot2::aes(x=rowMeans(e.i.imp), 
                                                          fill=as.factor(RCHOP21)))+
    ggplot2::geom_histogram(color="#e9ecef", alpha=0.6, binwidth=0.02)+
    ggplot2::theme_light()+
    ggplot2::theme(legend.title=ggplot2::element_blank(), 
                   text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12))+
    ggplot2::scale_fill_manual(values=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                               labels=c("6x R-CHOP21", "6x R-CHOP21 + 2R"))+
    ggplot2::ylab("Frequency")+
    ggplot2::xlab("Propensity score")+
    ggplot2::xlim(c(0, 1))
  ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/Figure.S2.at.landmark.", 
                         landmark, ".png"),
          plot=overlap.assumption.plot, 
          width=8, height=6, dpi=300)
  
  ##### Check balance before and after weighting using standardized mean difference
  # define number of quartiles
  g <- 4
  main.titles <- c("0-1", "2", "3", "4-5")
  
  # covariates
  vars <- c("geslacht", 
            "ipi_ldh",
            "ipi_ps",
            "ipi_extra",
            "malignancy", 
            "center",
            "lft", 
            paste0("region", 1:9), 
            paste0("stage", 2:4), 
            "ses.low", "ses.medium", "ses.high")
  
  # construct a table
  tabUnmatched.imp <- c()
  tabWeighted.imp <- c()
  for (imp in 1:m){
    # select ith imputed data set
    imp.i <- mice::complete(DLBCL, imp)[-omit.before.landmark,]
    
    # unweighted data
    tabUnmatched.imp <- cbind(tabUnmatched.imp, 
                              as.numeric(tableone::ExtractSmd(tableone::CreateTableOne(vars = vars, 
                                         strata = "RCHOP21", 
                                         data = imp.i, 
                                         test=FALSE))))
    
    # weighted data
    weighted.data.imp <- survey::svydesign(ids = ~ 1, 
                                         data = imp.i,
                                         weights = ~ stabilized.w.i.imp[, imp])
    # construct a table
    tabWeighted.imp <- cbind(tabWeighted.imp, 
                             as.numeric(tableone::ExtractSmd(tableone::svyCreateTableOne(vars = vars, 
                                         strata = "RCHOP21", 
                                         data = weighted.data.imp, 
                                         test = FALSE))))
  
  }
  tabUnmatched <- rowMeans(tabUnmatched.imp)
  tabWeighted <- rowMeans(tabWeighted.imp)
  
  # love plot for propensity scores based on all patients
  love.df <- data.frame(names=c("Females", 
                                "Elevated serum LDH", 
                                "Poor performance status", 
                                "At least one extranodal sites", 
                                "At least one previous malignancy", 
                                "Treatment at an academic center", 
                                "Age", 
                                paste("Region of treatment", 1:9),
                                paste("Ann Arbor stage", 2:4),
                                "Low SES", "Medium SES", "High SES"),
                        unweighted=tabUnmatched,
                        weighted=tabWeighted,
                        diff=tabUnmatched-tabWeighted)
  colnames(love.df) <- c("names", "unweighted", "weighted", "difference")
  ordered.love.df <- love.df[order(love.df$difference, decreasing=FALSE),]
  cat("Maximum Standardized Mean Difference:", max(ordered.love.df$weighted), "\n")
  
  # ensure right order
  ordered.love.df$names <- factor(ordered.love.df$names, levels=ordered.love.df$names) 
  ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/Figure.S3.at.landmark.", landmark, ".png"),
         plot=ggplot2::ggplot(data=ordered.love.df, ggplot2::aes(y=names, x=unweighted))+
               ggplot2::geom_vline(xintercept=0, linetype="solid")+
               ggplot2::geom_vline(xintercept=0.1, linetype="dashed")+
               ggplot2::geom_point(x=ordered.love.df$unweighted, colour="#EC7F12", size=3)+
               ggplot2::geom_point(x=ordered.love.df$weighted, colour="#9161BD", size=3)+
               ggplot2::ggtitle("Covariate balance for all patients")+
               ggplot2::xlab("Standardized mean difference")+
               ggplot2::ylab("")+
               ggplot2::scale_x_continuous(limits=c(0, 0.7),
                                           breaks=seq(0, 0.7, 0.1))+
               ggplot2::theme_classic()+
               ggplot2::theme(plot.title=element_text(hjust=0.5),
                              text=ggplot2::element_text(size=17),
                              axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
                              axis.line.y=element_blank()),
         width=8, height=6, dpi=300)
  
  # EFS outcome
  # The event-free survival indicator (efsi) is 1 if the patient has a 
  # recurrence or if there is no response to initial treatment and second line 
  # treatment is administered, and 0 otherwise. 
  single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$S.EFS <- survival::Surv(event=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$efsi, 
                                           time=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$EFS.time)
  med.EFS.time <- stats::quantile(prodlim::prodlim(prodlim::Hist(EFS.time, efsi==1)~1, 
                                                   data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark, reverse=TRUE))$quantiles.survival
  # OS outcome
  # The overall survival indicator (dood) is 1 if a patient died of any cause, 
  # and 0 otherwise
  single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$S.OS <- survival::Surv(event=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$dood, 
                                          time=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$OS.time)
  med.FU.time <- stats::quantile(prodlim::prodlim(prodlim::Hist(OS.time, dood==1)~1, 
                                                  data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark, reverse=TRUE))$quantiles.survival
  cat(" Median EFS:", paste0(sprintf("%.2f", med.EFS.time[3, "quantile"]), ", IQR: ",
         sprintf("%.2f", med.EFS.time[4, "quantile"]), "-",
         sprintf("%.2f", med.EFS.time[2, "quantile"])), "\n",
         "Median OS:", paste0(sprintf("%.2f", med.FU.time[3, "quantile"]), ", IQR: ",
         sprintf("%.2f", med.FU.time[4, "quantile"]), "-",
         sprintf("%.2f", med.FU.time[2, "quantile"])), "\n")
  save(DLBCL, file=paste0(file.path, "Data/imputed.DLBCL.Rdata"), compress=TRUE)
  
  # for each outcome, show Kaplan-Meier curves with statistics
  for (outcome in ylabs$outcome){
    # Survival outcome
    S.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$S.", outcome)))
    
    # Set the censoring of patients with follow-up time more than x years to "censored"
    S.temp[S.temp[,1]>limit_year, 2] <- 0
    # Set the follow-up time to x years for patients with follow-up time more than x years.
    S.temp[S.temp[,1]>limit_year, 1] <- limit_year
    assign(paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit"), S.temp)
    
    # Kaplan-Meier plots
    km_unweighted <- survival::survfit(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                            data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark, 
                            robust=TRUE, type="kaplan-meier")
    km <- survival::survfit(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                            data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark, 
                            weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp),
                            robust=TRUE, type="kaplan-meier", conf.type="log")
    assign(paste0("km_", outcome), km)
  
    # Kaplan-Meier estimates at x-years
    treat <- summary(km, times=limit_year)
    ARD <- diff(treat$surv)
    ARD_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.1f", ARD*100), "%")
    assign(paste0("ARD_", outcome), ARD)
    ARD_se <- sqrt(sum((treat$std.err)^2))
    ARD_CI_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.1f", (ARD-1.96*ARD_se)*100),
                     "-", sprintf("%.1f", (ARD+1.96*ARD_se)*100))
    assign(paste0("ARD_CI_", outcome), ARD_CI_text)
      
    # Log-rank test using stabilized weights is rejected,
    # thus the survival between the two treatment groups is significantly different
    LRT <- RISCA::ipw.log.rank(times=eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit[, 1]"))), 
                               failures=eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit[, 2]"))),
                               variable=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark$RCHOP21, 
                               weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp))
    LRT_text <- sprintf("%.2f", LRT$p.value)
    
    # Univariate Cox proportional hazards model with stabilized weights
    cox <- survival::coxph(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                           data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark,
                           weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp),
                           robust=TRUE)
    HR <- exp(coef(cox))
    HR_text <- sprintf("%.2f", HR)
    HR_text_lower <- sprintf("%.2f", exp(confint(cox)[, "2.5 %"]))
    HR_text_upper <- sprintf("%.2f", exp(confint(cox)[, "97.5 %"]))
    
    # Restricted Mean Survival Time analysis
    RMST <- survival:::survmean(km, rmean=limit_year)
    dRMST <- diff(RMST$matrix[, "rmean"])
    dRMST_text <- sprintf("%.2f", dRMST)
    assign(paste0("dRMST_", outcome), dRMST_text)
    dRMST_se <- RMST$matrix[, "se(rmean)"]
    dRMST_CI_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.2f", dRMST-1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_se^2))), 
                            "-", sprintf("%.2f", dRMST+1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_se^2))))
    assign(paste0("dRMST_CI_", outcome), dRMST_CI_text)
    
    # Kaplan-Meier plot
    km_plot <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km,
                                    palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                    ggtheme = theme(
                                      axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                                      panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                      plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                      panel.grid.major = element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                      panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                      legend.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                      legend.box.background = element_rect(color = NA, fill='white') #white legend panel
                                    ),
                                    legend.labs=c("6x R-CHOP21", "6x R-CHOP21+2R"),
                                    xlab="",
                                    ylab=ylabs[ylabs$outcome==outcome, "label"],
                                    risk.table=FALSE, conf.int="True",
                                    robust=TRUE, pval=FALSE)$plot+
                  ggplot2::annotate("text", x=0, y=0.05,
                                    label=paste0("p-value of weighted log-rank test = ",
                                                 LRT_text, "\n",
                                                 "HR = ", HR_text,
                                                 paste0(", 95% CI: ",
                                                        HR_text_lower, "-",
                                                        HR_text_upper, "\n"),
                                                 "ARD = ", ARD_text, 
                                                 paste0(", 95% CI: ", ARD_CI_text), "\n",
                                                 "\u0394RMST = ", dRMST_text,
                                                 paste0(" years, 95% CI: ", dRMST_CI_text), "\n"),
                                    size=3.5, hjust=0)
    assign(paste0("km_plot_", outcome), km_plot)
    km_table <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km_unweighted,
                                      palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                      ggtheme = theme(
                                         axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                                         panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                         plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                         panel.grid.major = element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                         panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                         legend.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                         legend.box.background = element_rect(fill='white') #white legend panel
                                      ),
                                      legend.labs=c("-2R", "+2R"),
                                      xlab="Time in years",
                                      risk.table=TRUE,
                                      robust=TRUE,
                                      pval=FALSE)$table
    assign(paste0("km_table_", outcome), km_table)
  
    # Write results to Excel
    results.df <- data.frame(names=c("6x R-CHOP21", "6x R-CHOP21+2R", "Difference", "P-value"),
             KMest=c(sprintf("%.1f", treat$surv*100),
                     sprintf("%.1f", ARD*100),
                     LRT_text),
             KMCI=c(paste0(sprintf("%.1f", treat$lower*100), 
                           "-", sprintf("%.1f", treat$upper*100)),
                    ARD_CI_text, 
                    ""),
             Coxest=c("(ref)",
                      HR_text,
                      "",
                      as.numeric(sprintf("%.2f", summary(cox)$robscore["pvalue"]))),
             CoxCI=c("",
                     paste0(HR_text_lower, "-",
                            HR_text_upper),
                     "",
                     ""),
             RMSTest=c(sprintf("%.2f", RMST$matrix[1, "rmean"]),
                       sprintf("%.2f", RMST$matrix[2, "rmean"]),
                       dRMST_text,
                       ""),
             RMSTCI=c("",
                      "",
                      dRMST_CI_text,
                      ""))
    print(results.df)
    openxlsx::write.xlsx(x=results.df,
             file=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/overall.", outcome , ".at.landmark.", landmark, ".xlsx"),
             sheetName=outcome)
  }
  
  # PH.assumption plot
  png(file=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/PH.assumption.at.landmark.", landmark, ".png"),
      width=600, height=300)
  par(mfrow=c(1, 2))
  outcome <- "EFS"
  plot(survival::cox.zph(survival::coxph(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                           data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark,
                           weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp),
                           robust=TRUE)), main="a. Event-free survival")
  outcome <- "OS"
  plot(survival::cox.zph(survival::coxph(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                           data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark,
                           weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp),
                           robust=TRUE)), main="b. Overall survival")
  grDevices::dev.off()
  
  # save Kaplan-Meier plot
  ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/Figure.2.at.landmark.", landmark, ".png"),
         plot=ggpubr::ggarrange(km_plot_EFS,
                                km_plot_OS,
                                km_table_EFS,
                                km_table_OS,
                                nrow=2, ncol=2, align="h", labels=c("A", "B"),
                                common.legend=TRUE, legend="top", heights=c(1, 0.3)),
         width=8, height=6, dpi=300)
  
  ###
  ### Subgroup analysis stratified by IPI score
  ###
  # obtain average IPI score across multiple imputations
  comb.ipi.imp <- c()
  for (imp in 1:m){
    comb.ipi.imp <- cbind(comb.ipi.imp, 
                          mice::complete(DLBCL, imp)[-omit.before.landmark, "ipi_score"])
  }
  combined.IPI <- round(rowMeans(comb.ipi.imp), 0)
  
  for (outcome in ylabs$outcome){
    # estimate treatment effect in each quartile
    KM_est_quartile <- c()
    plot_KM <- list()
    table_KM <- list()
    HR_quartile <- c()
    HR_quartile_lower <- c()
    HR_quartile_upper <- c()
    dRMST_quartiles <- c()
    dRMST_quartiles_lower <- c()
    dRMST_quartiles_upper <- c()
    LRT_stat_quartile <- c()
    LRT_p_quartile <- c()
    for (ipi.i in 1:g){
      # select data for only ith quartile
      quartile.DLBCL <- single.imp.DLBCL.landmark[combined.IPI==ipi.i,]
      quartile.stabilized.w.i <- rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp[combined.IPI==ipi.i,])
      
      # Survival outcome
      S.quartile <- eval(parse(text=paste0("quartile.DLBCL$S.", outcome)))
      # Set the censoring of patients with follow-up time more than x years to "censored"
      S.quartile[S.quartile[,1]>limit_year, 2] <- 0
      # Set the follow-up time to x years for patients with follow-up time more than x years.
      S.quartile[S.quartile[,1]>limit_year, 1] <- limit_year
      quartile.DLBCL$S.quartile <- S.quartile
  
      # event-free survival at 5 years
      km_quartile_unweighted <- survival::survfit(S.quartile~RCHOP21, 
                                       data=quartile.DLBCL, robust=TRUE,
                                       type="kaplan-meier")
      km_quartile <- survival::survfit(S.quartile~RCHOP21, 
                                       data=quartile.DLBCL, robust=TRUE,
                                       weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i,
                                       type="kaplan-meier", conf.type="log")
      # save survival
      treat_quartile <- summary(km_quartile, times = limit_year)
      KM_est_quartile <- rbind(KM_est_quartile,
                               cbind(treat_quartile$surv, treat_quartile$std.err,
                                     treat_quartile$lower, treat_quartile$upper))
      
      # log-rank test
      LRT_quartile <- RISCA::ipw.log.rank(times=S.quartile[, 1], failures=S.quartile[, 2],
                        variable=quartile.DLBCL$RCHOP21,
                        weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i)
      LRT_stat_quartile <- c(LRT_stat_quartile, LRT_quartile$statistic)
      LRT_p_quartile <- c(LRT_p_quartile, LRT_quartile$p.value)
  
      # univariate cox
      cox_quartile <- survival::coxph(S.quartile~RCHOP21, data=quartile.DLBCL,
                                    weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i,
                                    robust=TRUE)
      PH.assumption <- survival::cox.zph(cox_quartile)$table["RCHOP21", "p"]
  
      # save hazard ratios
      HR_quartile <- c(HR_quartile, as.numeric(exp(coef(cox_quartile)[1])))
      HR_quartile_lower <- c(HR_quartile_lower, as.numeric(exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,1])))
      HR_quartile_upper <- c(HR_quartile_upper, as.numeric(exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,2])))
  
      # RMST
      RMST_quartile <- survival:::survmean(km_quartile, rmean=limit_year)
      dRMST_Q <- diff(RMST_quartile$matrix[, "rmean"])
      dRMST_quartiles <- c(dRMST_quartiles, dRMST_Q)
      RMST_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", dRMST_Q)
      
      dRMST_Q_se <- RMST_quartile$matrix[, "se(rmean)"]
      dRMST_quartiles_lower <- c(dRMST_quartiles_lower, dRMST_Q-1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_Q_se^2)))
      dRMST_quartiles_upper <- c(dRMST_quartiles_upper, dRMST_Q+1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_Q_se^2)))
      
      # make text for KM plots
      LRT_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", LRT_quartile$p.value)
      HR_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(coef(cox_quartile)[1]))
      HR_text_quartile_lower <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,1]))
      HR_text_quartile_upper <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,2]))
      
      # save Kaplan-Meier plots
      plot_KM[[ipi.i]] <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km_quartile, 
                                                conf.int="True",
                                                palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                                ggtheme = ggplot2::theme(
                                                   axis.line = ggplot2::element_line(colour = "black"),
                                                   panel.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                                   plot.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                                   panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                                   panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                                   legend.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                                   legend.box.background = ggplot2::element_rect(km_plot, fill='white') #white legend panel
                                                ),
                                                ylim=c(0, 1), risk.table=TRUE)$plot+
      ggplot2::theme(legend.position = "none")+
      ggplot2::ylab(ylabs[ylabs$outcome==outcome, "label"])+
      ggplot2::xlab("")+
      ggplot2::theme(plot.title=ggplot2::element_text(hjust=0.5, size=10),
             axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
             axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
             axis.text.y=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
             axis.title.y=ggplot2::element_text(size=10))
      # ggplot2::ggtitle(paste0("IPI-score ", ifelse(ipi.i==1, "0-1",
      #                                              ifelse(ipi.i==4, "4-5", 
      #                                                     ipi.i)), ", (N=", nrow(quartile.DLBCL), ")")) 
              
      # save Kaplan-Meier risk table
      table_KM[[ipi.i]] <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km_quartile_unweighted,
        palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
        ggtheme = theme(axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                        axis.text.y = ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
                        axis.title.y = ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
                        axis.line.y = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        axis.ticks.y = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        axis.line.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        axis.ticks.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        axis.title.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                        panel.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                        plot.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                        panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                        panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                        legend.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                        legend.box.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white') #white legend panel
        ),
        legend.labs=c("-2R", "+2R"),
        xlab="Time in years",
        risk.table=TRUE,
        risk.table.title=element_blank(),
        risk.table.fontsize=3,
        robust=TRUE, pval=FALSE)$table
      
      # save for presentation
      if (landmark==42){
        ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Presentation Plots/", 
                             outcome, ".IPI.score.", ipi.i, ".png"),
           plot=ggpubr::ggarrange(plot_KM[[ipi.i]],
                                  table_KM[[ipi.i]],
                                  nrow=2, ncol=1, align="h",
                                  common.legend=TRUE, legend="top", heights=c(1, 0.3)),
           width=4.5, height=5, dpi=300)  
      }
    }
  
    # combine Kaplan-Meier estimates into one data frame
    KM_est_quartile <- cbind(KM_est_quartile, rep(c(0, 1), g))
    KM_est_quartile <- cbind(KM_est_quartile, rep(1:g, each=2))
    colnames(KM_est_quartile) <- c("estimate", "sd", "lower", "upper", "treatment", "risk.group")
    KM_est_quartile <- as.data.frame(KM_est_quartile)
    assign(paste0("KM_est_quartile_", outcome), KM_est_quartile)
  
    # combine hazard ratios into one data frame
    HR_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=HR_quartile, 
                                 lower=HR_quartile_lower, upper=HR_quartile_upper)
  
    # combine RMST into one data frame
    dRMST_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=dRMST_quartiles, 
                                   lower=dRMST_quartiles_lower, upper=dRMST_quartiles_upper)
    assign(paste0("dRMST_df_quartile_", outcome), dRMST_df_quartile)
    
    # Calculate the absolute difference in event-free survival, i.e. benefit and harm.
    diff <- c()
    j <- 1
    for (i in seq(from=1, to=nrow(KM_est_quartile), by=2)){
      diff <- rbind(diff, KM_est_quartile[i+1,]-KM_est_quartile[i,])
  
      # standard deviation of difference is square root of sum of variances
      diff[j, "sd"] <- sqrt(KM_est_quartile[i+1, "sd"]^2+KM_est_quartile[i, "sd"]^2)
      diff[j, "lower"] <- diff[j, "estimate"]-1.96*diff[j, "sd"]
      diff[j, "upper"] <- diff[j, "estimate"]+1.96*diff[j, "sd"]
      j <- j + 1
    }
    diff <- as.data.frame(diff)
    diff$risk.group <- 1:g
    ARD_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=diff$estimate*100, 
                                  lower=diff$lower*100, upper=diff$upper*100)
    assign(paste0("ARD_df_quartile_", outcome), ARD_df_quartile)
  
    # Write results to Excel
    results.df.q <- data.frame(cbind(c(rep("ARD", 4), rep("HR", 4), rep("RMST", 4)),
                                rbind(ARD_df_quartile,
                                      HR_df_quartile,
                                      dRMST_df_quartile)))
    results.df.q$text <- paste0(sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$estimate), ", 95% CI:", 
                                sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$lower), "; ", 
                                sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$upper))
    openxlsx::write.xlsx(results.df.q,
             file=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/IPI.stratified.for.", outcome, ".at.landmark.", landmark, ".xlsx"),
             sheetName=outcome)
    cat("ABSTRACT STATEMENT \nARD of Q4", 
        sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$estimate[4]), ", 95% CI:", 
        sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$lower[4]), "; ", 
        sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$upper[4]), "\n")

    # Kaplan-Meier plots
    KM_plots <- ggpubr::ggarrange(plot_KM[[1]]+ggplot2::labs(tag="A"),
                                  plot_KM[[2]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  plot_KM[[3]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  plot_KM[[4]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  ncol=4, nrow=1,
                                  widths=c(1, 0.8, 0.8, 0.8),
                                  align="h")
    
    # Kaplan-Meier tables
    table_KM_plots <- ggpubr::ggarrange(table_KM[[1]],
                                  table_KM[[2]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  table_KM[[3]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  table_KM[[4]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                    ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                  ncol=4, nrow=1,
                                  widths=c(1, 0.8, 0.8, 0.8),
                                  align="h")
    
    # plot for absolute reduction in survival
    avg.diff <- diff(summary(eval(parse(text=paste0("km_", outcome))),
                             times = limit_year)$surv)
    ARD.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=diff,
                                ggplot2::aes(x=factor(risk.group), y=estimate))+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=0)+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=avg.diff, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
      ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                             position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
      ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
      ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(diff$lower, -0.2), max(diff$upper, 0.4)),
                                  breaks=seq(-0.2, 0.4, 0.2),
                                  labels=scales::percent_format(accuracy=1))+
      ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                     axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                     panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                     plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                     panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                     panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
      ggplot2::ylab("ARD") + 
      ggplot2::theme(axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                     axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                     axis.ticks.x=ggplot2::element_blank())+
      ggplot2::labs(tag="C")
    
    # test for multiplicative HTE
    S.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit")))
    test.HR <- summary(coxph(S.temp ~ RCHOP21*combined.IPI, 
                             data=single.imp.DLBCL.landmark,
                             weights=rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.imp)))$coefficients[3, "Pr(>|z|)"]
    
    # create plot for hazard ratios
    hazard.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=HR_df_quartile, ggplot2::aes(x=risk.group, y=estimate))+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=1)+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=HR, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
      ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                             position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
      ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
      ggplot2::scale_x_discrete(limits=as.factor(1:g))+
      ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(HR_df_quartile$lower, 0.5), 
                                           max(HR_df_quartile$upper, 2)),
                                  breaks=seq(0.5, 2, 0.5),
                                  labels=scales::number_format(accuracy=0.01))+
      ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                      axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.ticks.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                      panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                      plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                      panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
      ggplot2::ylab("Hazard ratio")+
      ggplot2::geom_text(mapping=aes(x=g, y=2, 
                                     label=paste0("p-value = ", sprintf("%.2f", test.HR))),
                         hjust=0, size=3)+
      ggplot2::labs(tag="B")
  
    # create plot for RMST
    dRMST.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=dRMST_df_quartile, ggplot2::aes(x=risk.group, y=estimate))+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=0)+
      ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=dRMST, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
      ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                             position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
      ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
      ggplot2::scale_x_discrete(limits=c("1"="IPI score 0-1", "2"="IPI score 2", "3"="IPI score 3", "4"="IPI score 4-5"))+
      ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(dRMST_df_quartile$lower, -0.25), 
                                           max(dRMST_df_quartile$upper, 1)),
                                  breaks=seq(-0.25, 1, 0.25),
                                  labels=scales::number_format(accuracy=0.01))+
      ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                      axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                      panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                      plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                      panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
      ggplot2::xlab("IPI score")+
      ggplot2::ylab("\u0394RMST")+
      ggplot2::labs(tag="D")
    
    # save plot
    ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Plots/Figure.IPI-stratified.", outcome, ".at.landmark.", landmark, ".png"),
         plot=ggpubr::ggarrange(KM_plots, table_KM_plots,
                                hazard.plot / ARD.plot / dRMST.plot, 
                                nrow=3, ncol=1, heights=c(5, 2, 10)),
         width=8, height=8, dpi=300)
  }
}
